[{},{"attrs":{"title":"API: The ModuleContainer Class","description":"Nuxt ModuleContainer Class"},"body":"<h1><a id=\"modulecontainer-class\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#modulecontainer-class\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>ModuleContainer Class</h1><ul>\n<li>Source: <strong><a href=\"https://github.com/nuxt/nuxt.js/blob/dev/packages/core/src/module.js\">core/module.js</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All <a href=\"/guide/modules\">modules</a> will be called within context of <code>ModuleContainer</code> instance.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"tapable-plugins\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#tapable-plugins\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Tapable plugins</h2><p>We can register hooks on certain life cycle events.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\">nuxt.moduleContainer.plugin(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'ready'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">async</span> moduleContainer =&gt; {\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Do this after all modules where ready</span>\n})</code></pre><p>Inside <a href=\"/guide/modules\">modules</a> context we can use this instead:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">this</span>.plugin(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'ready'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">async</span> moduleContainer =&gt; {\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Do this after all modules where ready</span>\n})</code></pre><table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Plugin</th>\n<th>Arguments</th>\n<th>When</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><code>ready</code></td>\n<td>moduleContainer</td>\n<td>All modules in <code>nuxt.config.js</code> has been initialized</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2><a id=\"methods\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#methods\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Methods</h2><h3><a id=\"addvendor-vendor-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#addvendor-vendor-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>addVendor (vendor)</h3><p><strong>Deprecated as <code>vendor</code> isn&#39;t used anymore</strong></p>\n<p>Adds to <code>options.build.vendor</code> and apply unique filter.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"addtemplate-template-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#addtemplate-template-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>addTemplate (template)</h3><ul>\n<li><strong>template</strong>: <code>String</code> or <code>Object</code><ul>\n<li><code>src</code></li>\n<li><code>options</code></li>\n<li><code>fileName</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Renders given template using <a href=\"https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.4#template\">lodash template</a> during build into project <code>buildDir</code> (<code>.nuxt</code>).</p>\n<p>If <code>fileName</code> is not provided or <code>template</code> is string, target file name defaults to <code>[dirName].[fileName].[pathHash].[ext]</code>.</p>\n<p>This method returns final <code>{ dist, src, options }</code> object.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"addplugin-template-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#addplugin-template-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>addPlugin (template)</h3><p>Registers a plugin using <code>addTemplate</code> and adds it to first of <code>plugins[]</code> option.</p>\n<p>You can use <code>template.ssr: false</code> to disable plugin including in SSR bundle.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"addservermiddleware-middleware-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#addservermiddleware-middleware-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>addServerMiddleware (middleware)</h3><p>Pushes middleware into <a href=\"/api/configuration-servermiddleware\">options.serverMiddleware</a>.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"extendbuild-fn-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#extendbuild-fn-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>extendBuild (fn)</h3><p>Allows easily extending webpack build config by chaining <a href=\"/api/configuration-build#extend\">options.build.extend</a> function.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"extendroutes-fn-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#extendroutes-fn-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>extendRoutes (fn)</h3><p>Allows easily extending routes by chaining <a href=\"/api/configuration-router#extendroutes\">options.build.extendRoutes</a> function.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"addmodule-moduleopts-requireonce-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#addmodule-moduleopts-requireonce-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>addModule (moduleOpts, requireOnce)</h3><p><em>Async function</em></p>\n<p>Registers a module. <code>moduleOpts</code> can be a string or an array (<code>[src, options]</code>). \nIf <code>requireOnce</code> is <code>true</code> and the resolved module exports <code>meta</code>, it prevents registering same module twice.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"requiremodule-moduleopts-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#requiremodule-moduleopts-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>requireModule (moduleOpts)</h3><p><em>Async function</em></p>\n<p>Is a shortcut for <code>addModule(moduleOpts, true)</code></p>\n<h2><a id=\"hooks\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#hooks\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Hooks</h2><p>We can register hooks on certain life cycle events.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Hook</th>\n<th>Arguments</th>\n<th>When</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><code>modules:before</code></td>\n<td>(moduleContainer, options)</td>\n<td>Called before creating ModuleContainer class, useful to overload methods and options.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>modules:done</code></td>\n<td>(moduleContainer)</td>\n<td>Called when all modules have been loaded.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n","docLink":"https://github.com/nuxt/docs/blob/master/en/api/internals-module-container.md"}]